Package edu.jhu.rebar

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Corpus
    Interface for reading and writing from a "REBAR Corpus".
    Corpus.DiffWriter
    Interface used by RPC to write "diffs", i.e., monotonic changes to communications.
    Corpus.Initializer
    Interface used to initialize a new corpus by defining the set of communications that it contains.
    Corpus.Reader
    Interface for "corpus readers", which are used to read a communications from a corpus, including the output of a specified set of stages.
    Corpus.Writer
    Interface for "corpus writers," which are used to add the output of a processing stage to some or all of the communications in a corpus.
    CorpusFactory
    An interface for creating a "corpus factory", a top level corpus object that can manage corpora in the backend (e.g., corpus creation and deletion).
    Graph
    Interface for reading and writing from a "REBAR Knowledge Graph".
    Graph.DiffWriter
    Interface used by RPC to write "diffs", i.e., monotonic changes to edges and verticess.
    Graph.EdgeLoader  
    Graph.Initializer
    Interface used to initialize a new graph by defining the set of vertices that it contains.
    Graph.Reader
    Interface for "graph readers", which are used to read vertices and edges from a graph, including the output of a specified set of stages.
    Graph.VertexLoader  
    Graph.Writer
    Interface for "graph writers," which are used to add the output of a processing stage to some or all of the vertices in a graph.
    IndexedTokenization.TokenSequence  
    Stage
    A record for a processing stage, which adds information to a REBAR corpus or knowledge graph.
    StagedDataCollection
    Base interface for corpora and graphs.
